  "prompt": "What is luvox good for?",
  "response": "Luvox, also known by its generic name fluvoxamine, is an antidepressant medication that belongs to the class of drugs called selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors (SSRIs). It is primarily used to treat the following conditions:\n\n1. **Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder (OCD):** Luvox is approved for the treatment of OCD in both adults and children aged 8 and older. It helps reduce the frequency and intensity of obsessive thoughts and compulsive behaviors.\n\n2. **Depression:** While not as commonly prescribed for depression as some other SSRIs, Luvox can be used to treat major depressive disorder.\n\n3. **Social Anxiety Disorder (SAD):** In some countries, Luvox is approved for the treatment of social anxiety disorder.\n\n4. **Panic Disorder:** It may be used off-label to treat panic disorder.\n\nLuvox works by increasing the levels of serotonin in the brain, which helps improve mood and reduce anxiety. As with any medication, it's important to use Luvox under the guidance of a healthcare professional who can monitor its effects and adjust the dosage as needed.",
